    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Crypto is okay for small stuff, but anyone with my level of clearance/history knows they can track on-chain movements if they're looking hard enough. I'm more worried about the institutional side. If these cells have infiltrated the standard clearing houses, even a wallet shuffle won't matter if they flag the initial conversion. Have you heard anything about specific banking protocols that these types of organizations use to flag \"irregular\" high-net-worth movements? I need to know what they're looking for so I can stay under the radar.",
